<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF02701659BFDCD837293B5" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF02701659BFDCD80AA92ED" blockId="39.[151,1436,606,705]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF02701659BFDCD80CF9255" authority="Ahl, 1931" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,471,607,633]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noblei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701659BFDCD80479255" box="[151,351,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius noblei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF027016469FDCD80CF9255" author="Ahl" box="[357,471,607,633]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFF0270164EEFDCD83779255" box="[482,623,606,633]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/ZMB85765" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">ZMB 85765</accessionNumber>
, “Kilwa, 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270167D4FDCD82B19255" box="[728,937,607,633]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Deutsch-Ostafrika</collectingCountry>
” 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270166B4FDCD85059255" box="[952,1053,607,633]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF027016127FDCD859A9255" box="[1067,1154,607,633]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
). Colour in alcohol: Uniform yellow-brown. A silver-white stripe runs from the side of the snout, over the upper eyelid to form a larger mark behind the eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF02701659BFD7D837293B5" blockId="39.[151,1437,751,1173]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
Sequences were available from Nhica and Palma, 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270167EFFD7D826F9325" box="[739,887,751,777]" name="Mozambique" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF0270166A1FD7D85FC9324" baseAuthorityName="Perret" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[941,1252,751,777]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270166A1FD7D85309325" box="[941,1064,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF027016157FD7D85FC9324" box="[1115,1252,751,776]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and Nhica do Rovuma (as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF027016420FC8183B49300" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1854" box="[300,684,787,813]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="marmoratus" subSpecies="taeniatus">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF027016420FC8183B49300" box="[300,684,787,813]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius marmoratus taeniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270167CAFC8182469301" box="[710,862,787,813]" name="Mozambique" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
. The two sequences from Nhica (
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFF0270161EAFC8184719301" box="[1254,1385,787,813]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MG829620" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">MG829620</accessionNumber>
and 
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFF02701659BFCA48002937D" box="[151,282,822,849]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MK509512" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">MK509512</accessionNumber>
) were derived from the same specimen (MNHNP 2010.185). The minimum uncorrected 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF027016012FCA5842D937C" box="[1310,1333,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 4.2–6.9% (
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF027016718FCC983729359" box="[532,618,859,885]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Presently this species is only known from southern coastal 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF027016005FCC984769359" box="[1289,1390,859,885]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and northern coastal 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF02701645EFCED80FE93B5" box="[338,486,895,921]" name="Mozambique" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="15FFD3DDFFF0270164F9FCED834593B5" box="[501,605,895,921]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-63@40.[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius noblei (A), H. goetzei (B), H. spatzi (C) and H. dintelmanni (D). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538300/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF0270165CBFC3182D694B9" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF0270165CBFC3185EB9429" blockId="39.[151,1437,751,1173]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
The nearest described taxon to this clade is 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF0270167A9FC3182FA9391" authority="Ahl, 1931" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[677,994,931,957]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noblei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270167A9FC3182749391" box="[677,876,931,957]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius noblei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF02701667CFC3182FA9391" author="Ahl" box="[880,994,931,957]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The description matches the specimens collected and sequenced from northern 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF027016759FC5583F193CD" box="[597,745,967,993]" name="Mozambique" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF0270167FBFC55825493CD" box="[759,844,967,993]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,466,492]" captionTargetId="graphics-52@4.[151,2038,1007,1693]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Species assignments, GenBank identifications, GenBank accession numbers, Voucher numbers, localities, map coordinates and sources for 16S rRNA sequences." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFD32722659BFE4086D291C0" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFD32722659BFE4086D291C0">Table 1</tableCitation>
). The pattern elements in the description of the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFF027016060FC55848493CD" box="[1388,1436,967,993]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF0270165BAFC7980069429" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[182,286,1003,1029]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noblei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270165BAFC7980069429" box="[182,286,1003,1029]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">H. noblei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are a uniform back, with a transverse silver stripe forming a large mark behind the eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF0270165CBFB9D82D694B9" blockId="39.[151,1437,751,1173]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<location id="881B9983FFF0270165CBFB9D81EB9405" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFF02701659BFD8482D694B9:881B9983FFF0270165CBFB9D81EB9405" box="[199,243,1039,1065]" country="Mozambique" county="Palma" latitude="-0.05" longLatPrecision="555" longitude="40.4732" municipality="Afungi Peninsula" name="The" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">The</location>
advertisement call (no voucher) was recorded on the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6D1F5522FFF027016649FB9D85109405" box="[837,1032,1039,1065]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Afungi Peninsula</collectingMunicipality>
at 
<collectingCounty id="641AB7D4FFF027016125FB9D856A9405" box="[1065,1138,1039,1065]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Palma</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF027016170FB9D84089405" box="[1148,1296,1039,1065]" name="Mozambique" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF027016012FB9C84809405" box="[1310,1432,1038,1065]" degrees="10.8456" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" precision="5" value="-10.8456">10.8456°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF02701659BFBA1800A9461" box="[151,274,1075,1101]" degrees="40.4732" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" precision="5" value="40.4732">40.4732°E</geoCoordinate>
). The call is a long (
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF0270164F8FBA183209461" box="[500,568,1075,1101]" degrees="0.08" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" precision="555" value="-0.08">0.08 s</geoCoordinate>
) whistle, frequency modulated, with the emphasised frequency at 3500 
<collectorName id="2031AA8EFFF027016051FBA184859461" box="[1373,1437,1075,1101]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hz. A</collectorName>
typical call starts at 3000 Hz, and rises steeply in pitch to 3595 Hz in 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF027016698FBC582CF945D" box="[916,983,1111,1137]" degrees="0.03" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" precision="555" value="-0.03">0.03 s</geoCoordinate>
, then maintains that pitch for 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFF02701602EFBC4847E945D" box="[1314,1382,1110,1137]" degrees="0.05" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" precision="555" value="-0.05">0.05 s</geoCoordinate>
. The emphasised frequency varies in the population from 3500 Hz to 4565 Hz.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
